</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34A6541882EEE40FF62FF5C6E12FE88" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BEF36CA882EEE40FF62FF5C6E12FE88" blockId="6.[151,1437,150,537]" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">
<emphasis id="B924EAD8882EEE40FF62FF5C6D0FFF79" bold="true" box="[199,322,150,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D49882EEE40FC98FF5D68A5FF78" authority="(Kulczynski, 1903)" baseAuthorityName="Kulczynski" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[829,1256,151,177]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Maimuna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cretica">
<emphasis id="B924EAD8882EEE40FC98FF5D684DFF79" box="[829,1024,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">Maimuna cretica</emphasis>
(Kulczyński, 1903)
</taxonomicName>
, having a wide median apophysis of the male palp and similar shapes of the epigyne and vulva. The male can be separated by (1) the fan-shaped median apophysis and (2) the large, straight and well sclerotized terminal end of the ventral part of the conductor (
<figureCitation id="136B2A4F882EEE40FE9AFEC96DDBFED4" box="[319,406,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[320,1267,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-31@2.[320,1267,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 4–12. 4–6 Maimuna anatolica sp. n., holotype male, right palp (flipped). 7–9 Maimuna cariae, paratype male, left palp. 10–12 Maimuna vestita, male, left palp. 1,7, 10 ventral 5, 8, 11 retrolateral; 6, 9, 12 prolateral. Scale line: 0.5 mm" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6411052" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6411052/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">Figs 10</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="136B2A4F882EEE40FE07FEC96D8FFED4" box="[418,450,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–27" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1781,1805]" captionTargetBox="[156,1433,181,1758]" captionTargetId="figure-31@4.[151,1435,181,1758]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 21–27. 21–23 Maimuna anatolica sp. n., male holotype. 24–25 Maimuna anatolica sp. n., female paratype. 26 Maimuna cariae, male paratype. 27 Maimuna vestita, male. 21, 26–27 palp, ventral. 22 palp prolateral. 23 palp retrolateral. 24 epigyne, ventral view. 25 vulva, dorsal view. Scale line: 0.5 mm" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6411056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6411056/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">27</figureCitation>
). The female differs by the wide, oval epigynal plate, wider than the epigynal hood (
<figureCitation id="136B2A4F882EEE40FAD0FEC96CF8FE88" captionStart="FIGURES 13–20" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[302,1285,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-16@3.[302,1285,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 13–20. 13–16 Maimuna anatolica sp. n., females paratypes. 17–18 Maimuna cariae, female paratype. 19–20 Maimuna vestita, female. 13–15, 17, 19 epigyne, ventral view; 16, 18, 20 vulva, dorsal view. Scale line: 0.5 mm" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6411054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6411054/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">Fig 19</figureCitation>
), and the narrow receptacles (
<figureCitation id="136B2A4F882EEE40FDA0FEED6E1EFE88" box="[517,595,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–20" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[302,1285,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-16@3.[302,1285,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 13–20. 13–16 Maimuna anatolica sp. n., females paratypes. 17–18 Maimuna cariae, female paratype. 19–20 Maimuna vestita, female. 13–15, 17, 19 epigyne, ventral view; 16, 18, 20 vulva, dorsal view. Scale line: 0.5 mm" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6411054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6411054/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">Fig 20</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34A6541882EEE40FF62FE806F60FEAC" box="[199,813,330,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEF36CA882EEE40FF62FE806F60FEAC" blockId="6.[151,1437,150,537]" box="[199,813,330,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">
<emphasis id="B924EAD8882EEE40FF62FE806D14FEAD" bold="true" box="[199,345,330,356]" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">Description.</emphasis>
See Blaue (1980: 46, sub 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D49882EEE40FDDAFE816F51FEAD" authorityName=": Demir &amp; Seyyar" authorityYear="2017" box="[639,796,331,356]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Textrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vestita">
<emphasis id="B924EAD8882EEE40FDDAFE816F51FEAD" box="[639,796,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">Textrix vestita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34A6541882EEE40FF62FEA468EDFE64" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BEF36CA882EEE40FF62FEA468EDFE64" blockId="6.[151,1437,150,537]" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">
<emphasis id="B924EAD8882EEE40FF62FEA46D2CFE41" bold="true" box="[199,353,366,392]" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">Distribution.</emphasis>
Eastern Mediterranean, Balkan Peninsula, 
<collectingCountry id="F347765A882EEE40FCE3FEA56FE9FE40" box="[838,932,367,393]" name="Ukraine" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
. All of the records of 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D49882EEE40FB3CFEA56945FE41" authorityName=": Demir &amp; Seyyar" authorityYear="2017" box="[1177,1288,367,392]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Textrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vestita">
<emphasis id="B924EAD8882EEE40FB3CFEA56945FE41" box="[1177,1288,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">M. vestita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F347765A882EEE40FAE9FEA569D1FE40" box="[1356,1436,367,393]" name="Turkey" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">Turkey</collectingCountry>
are from the easternmost part of the country, near to the Mediterranean and Marmara coasts.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34A6541882EEE40FF62FE7D6F72FDD0" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BEF36CA882EEE40FF62FE7D6F72FDD0" blockId="6.[151,1437,150,537]" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">
<emphasis id="B924EAD8882EEE40FF62FE7D6D76FE18" bold="true" box="[199,315,439,465]" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">Remarks.</emphasis>
I was not able to examine the Turkish material of this species but the drawings provided by Brignoli (1976) and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B3B882EEE40FEBDFE116D8EFE3C" author="Lecigne, S." box="[280,451,475,501]" pageId="6" pageNumber="389" pagination="5 - 83" refId="ref3216" refString="Lecigne, S. (2011) Inventaire araneologique dans la Province d'Izmir (Turquie) (Arachnida, Araneae). Le bulletin d'Arthropoda, 46 (2), 5 - 83." type="journal article" year="2011">Lecigne (2011)</bibRefCitation>
leave no doubt about its identity. Since it is the 
<typeStatus id="54EB8868882EEE40FC7EFE116846FE3C" box="[987,1035,475,501]" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus, I provide new photographs and drawings based on specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="F347765A882EEE40FD4CFE356F71FDD0" box="[745,828,511,537]" name="Greece" pageId="6" pageNumber="389">Greece</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
